# [[Present participle]] of '''to [[smash]]'''.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-more}}

# Serving to [[smash]] (something).
#:''The boxer delivered a smashing blow to his opponent's head.''
# (''British informal'') [[Wonderful]], very [[good]] or [[impressive]].
#:''We had a smashing time at the zoo.''  Thought to be corruption of Irish ''is maith é sin'' (meaning "that's good")

